This command is used to visually see the differences between multiple branch commits.

Where you can choose final modification among the available options.

Once it's done. you commit the changes using $ git commit -m "Commit after solving conflicts"

After that you will get untracked file with extension .orig This file holds all the conflicts incase you want to change the data after commit.

You can simply add this filename into .gitignore file

And do final commit.
